## Context

**Plan References**:
- `.plan/2026-02-05-velvet-cascade/integrations.md` Browser automation section

**Key Points**:
- agent-browser uses Playwright under the hood
- Alternative to MCP Playwright server
- Uses ref-based element selection for LLM-friendly automation
- Requires Node.js and npx

## Notes

Installation:
```bash
npm install -g @vercel/agent-browser
# or use npx for on-demand execution
```

Configuration in `config/config.exs`:
```elixir
config :pag_server, :browser,
  command: "npx",
  args: ["@vercel/agent-browser"],
  headless: true,
  viewport: %{width: 1280, height: 720},
  timeout: 30_000
```

Test browser availability:
```bash
npx @vercel/agent-browser browse "https://example.com" \
  --snapshot --timeout 10000
```

